            <h2 id="stats" class="basic-header">Stats</h2>
            <h3>Intellect</h3>
            <p>Intellect increases your maximum Mana, increases your chance to critically strike with spells, and improves the rate at with you improve your Weapon Skills. You gain 15 Mana for each point of Intellect. Druids receive 1% Spell Critical Strike
                Chance for every 60 points of Intellect.</p>
            <p>In other words:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>1 Intellect=15 Mana</li>
                <li>60 Intellect= 1% Spell Critical Chance</li>
            </ul>
            <section>
                <h3>Spirit</h3>
                <p>Spirit increases Health regeneration while out of combat and increases Mana regeneration while not casting spells. Mana begins to regenerate via Spirit only when you have not cast any spells that cost Mana for 5 seconds</p>
                <p>After this, you'll begin to regenerate Mana every 2 seconds depending on if you are a caster or a Feral Druid:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>For a caster Druid: Spirit/4.5 + 15</li>
                    <li>For a Feral Druid: Spirit/5 + 15</li>
                </ul>
            </section>
            <section>
                <h3>Stamina</h3>
                <p>Stamina increases your maximum Health. You gain 10 Health for every point of Stamina.</p>
                <p>In other words:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>1 Stamina = 10 Health</li>
                </ul>
            </section>
            <section>
                <h2>Secondary Stats</h2>
                <h3>Healing Power</h3>
                <p>Healing Power increases how much your healing spells will heal your target. This is a very powerful stat for healing Druids. You'll be looking to gather as much of this as possible through gear and enchants.</p>
                <h3>Mana/5 Seconds</h3>
                <p>Also known as MP5, this stat will regenerate a certain amount of Mana every 5 seconds. This stat is independent of Spirit and the "Five Second Rule," working even while constantly casting in combat.</p>
                <h3>Spell Critical Chance</h3>
                <p> Spell Critical Strike increases your chance to strike a critical hit with spells. A critical spell hit deals 150% of a spell’s normal damage. You can gain Spell Critical Strike with Intellect or with raw Spell Critical Strike chance provided
                    on gear.
                </p>
            </section>
            <section>
                <h2>Stat Priority for Resto Druids</h2>
                <ol>
                    <li>Healing power</li>
                    <li>Mana/5 Seconds</li>
                    <li>Spirit</li>
                    <li>Intellect</li>
                    <li>Spell Crit</li>
                </ol>
            </section>
