            <h2 class="basic-header">Talents and Builds</h2>
            <section>
                <h3>Moonglow Build</h3>
                <img class="page-image" alt="moonglow" title="moonglow" src="../images/moonglow.png">
                <p>Early on in Classic, mana efficiency is critical. Your mana pool will be fairly small, and you won’t have easy access to items with healing power on them. This build centers around conserving mana by going into the Balance talent tree
                    to grab the talent Moonglow.</p>
            </section>
            <section>
                <h3>Regrowth/Nature's Grace(My current build)</h3>
                <img class="page-image" alt="regrowth/nature's grace" title="regrowth/nature's grace" src="../images/regrowth-nature.png">
                <p>This build focuses on the Regrowth and Nature's Grace interaction. Basically, Improved Regrowth increases the crit chance of Regrowth, which can then reduce the cast time of your next spell by 0.5 seconds due to Nature's Grace. That can
                    lead to one nasty fast Healing Touch. The downside to using this build is that it does require a bigger mana pool, which is why it is advised to wait until you and your tank have acquired more gear.</p>
            </section>
            <section>
